# API Standard

## Trigger Checklist

- User asks to standardize API responses or controller style.
- `Rule Guard` finds an API contract or controller-boundary violation.
- A controller accumulates orchestration, mapping, or Infrastructure wiring.
- A new endpoint needs consistent success and error response behavior.

## Enforce

- Keep controllers thin; move orchestration into Core services or use cases.
- Use the standard response envelope when the project expects one.
- Keep Infrastructure wiring in DI composition, not in controllers.
- Route unhandled failures through a global exception handler with safe client output.
- Re-check layering against `docs/rules/architecture-protocol.md`.

